Wash and dry all produce. Core, deseed, and thinly slice @green bell pepper{1}(thinly sliced). Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}(thinly sliced). Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(roughly chopped) leaves and tender stems.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tablespoon} and @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} (to taste). Stir in @water{}, 1 tsp at a time, until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{}.

Slice @grilling cheese{8%ounce} into 6 equal sized pieces (12 pieces for 4 servings). Drizzle on both sides with @olive oil{}, then sprinkle with half the @fajita spice blend{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest later). Rub to evenly coat grilling cheese in spice.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper, onion, remaining fajita spice, and a large pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are softened and beginning to char, about ~{8%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat (use a #nonstick pan{} if you have one). Add grilling cheese and sear until browned, ~{1-2%minutes} per side. (For 4 servings, sear in two batches.)

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave on high until warm, about ~{30%seconds}. Divide tortillas between plates. Top tortillas with one piece of grilling cheese each, then add veggies, crema, and cilantro.

> HelloFresh fans, meet your new favorite fajitas. These fajitas are extra special. Spice-rubbed grilling cheese is pan-seared to develop a deep brown crust while the inside gets all warm and melty. The killer queso is then piled into steamy tortillas along with a tangle of peppers and onions, a drizzle of hot sauce crema, and a sprinkle of fresh cilantro. It's a fiesta on your plate!